components.name: Wait for FTP File
components.description: Monitors the FTP server for the presence of vendor_inventory.csv and emits a detection signal.

upstream_policy.description: No upstream dependencies; this sensor starts the pipeline.

connections.purpose: Access FTP server to monitor and download files

components.name: Download Vendor File
components.description: Downloads the detected vendor_inventory.csv from the FTP server to a local temporary file.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after successful file detection by the FTP sensor.

connections.purpose: Access FTP server to download files

components.name: Cleanse Vendor Data
components.description: Removes null values from critical columns (product_id, quantity, price) in the downloaded vendor inventory CSV.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after the vendor file has been successfully downloaded.

components.name: Merge with Internal Inventory
components.description: Merges the cleansed vendor inventory data with internal inventory records on product_id to update stock levels and pricing.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after vendor data has been cleansed.

connections.purpose: Access internal inventory system for merging records

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

poke_interval.description: Interval in seconds between sensor polls

timeout.description: Maximum time in seconds to wait for the file before failing

destination_path.description: Local filesystem path where the downloaded vendor file will be stored

target_columns.description: List of column names to check for null values and cleanse

join_key.description: Column name used to join vendor data with internal inventory records

sources: Vendor inventory CSV file (vendor_inventory.csv) located on the external FTP server
sinks: Updated internal inventory records stored in the internal inventory database
